com.indooratlas.android

Interface IndoorAtlas


  • public interface IndoorAtlas
    Main entry point for interacting with IndoorAtlas positioning services. Use IndoorAtlasFactory to obtain instance of this class.

    In a typical flow, obtain instance of this class in Activity#onCreate and release it in Activity#onDestroy by calling tearDown(). Setting up the positioning session may take a moment so you can choose to start positioning in Activity#onResume and stopping it in Activity#onPause or start in Activity#onCreate and stop in Activity#onDestroy. The former is more battery friendly but getting the first fix after returning to activity may take longer. The latter is likely to consume more battery power but is able to provider higher accuracy positions faster, when returning to activity.

    In order to use this interface and start positioning, visit https://developer.indooratlas.com to obtain your API credentials and floor plan identifiers.

    • Method Detail

      • startPositioning

        void startPositioning(java.lang.String buildingId,
                      java.lang.String levelId,
                      java.lang.String floorplanId)
               throws IndoorAtlasException
        Starts a new positioning session. If positioning is already running, calling this methods has no effect.
        • IndoorAtlasListener.onServiceInitializing() gets called when initializing is started.
        • IndoorAtlasListener.onServiceInitialized() gets called after a successful session initialization.
        • IndoorAtlasListener.onInitializationFailed(String) gets called with error condition if initialization fails.
        Parameters:
        buildingId - a non null id of the building (see class comments for buildingId)
        levelId - a non null id of the level (see class comments for levelId)
        floorplanId - a non null id of the floor plan (see class comments for floorplanId)
        Throws:
        IndoorAtlasException

      • startPositioning

        Starts a new positioning session with custom parameters.

      • stopPositioning

        void stopPositioning()
        Stop positioning session. Once completed, IndoorAtlasListener.onServiceStopped() is invoked. You may restart positioning again with startPositioning(String, String, String).

      • setPreferMobileConnection

        void setPreferMobileConnection(boolean preferMobile)
        Set network preference to mobile hipri connection. This is also the default, if mobile hipri network is available on the platform. onNetworkChangeComplete is called on IndoorAtlasListener to inform about the result.

        Parameters:
        preferMobile - when true, sets network preference to mobile hipri connection, if mobile hipri network is available on the platform.

        When false, sets network preference to WiFi, even if Wifi network is not available.

      • tearDown

        void tearDown()
        Releases any resources used by the API. Positioning cannot be started after calling this method. A good place to invoke this method would be e.g. in Activity#onDestroy. See class documentation for more on how to use this class.

      • isCalibrationReady

        boolean isCalibrationReady()
        Note: since version 1.4, this method always returns true, positioning may be started at any time.

      • getCommunicationLatency

        float getCommunicationLatency()
        Query interface for approximate communication latency.
        Returns:
        current communication latency in seconds.

      • getBufferedQueueLength

        int getBufferedQueueLength()
        Query interface for getting number of queued sensor data packets.
        Returns:
        current amount of buffered messages. Returns -1 if there is no active positioning session.

        Parameters:

        longitude - in WGS84 coordinate system

      • submitExplicitPixelPosition

        void submitExplicitPixelPosition(int x,
                                 int y,
                                 float radiusInPixels)
        Hint a known position to the positioning system. Note that origin (0,0) is upper left corner of the original map image, un-rotated/scaled.
        Parameters:
        x - pixels in x-axis on floor plan image
        y - pixels in y-axis on floor plan image
        radiusInPixels - defines easing value in meters for the explicit position

      • submitExplicitMetricPosition

        void submitExplicitMetricPosition(int x,
                                  int y,
                                  float radiusInMeters)
        Hint a known position to the positioning system. Note that origin (0,0) is upper left corner of the original map image, un-rotated.
        Parameters:
        x - meters in x-axis on floor plan image, where origin (0,0) is upper left corner
        y - meters in y-axis on floor plan image, where origin (0,0) is upper left corner
        radiusInMeters - defines easing value in meters for the explicit position
